The variety of sauces is definitely the best part of Sticky's. I particularly liked the Chipotle Aoili and Sticky's sauces, and the Nashville Numb sauce is great if like extra spicy. The chicken itself was good, but nothing extraordinary by itself, same for the fries. Unfortunately, the restaurant itself was a disappointment especially if you have little kids. There were no high chairs (yet, apparently), so don't forget a stroller for little ones like we did. No changing tables in the bathrooms either. Prices are on the higher side too, considering there is no table service, but about on par for gourmet fast food. The worst part by far, though, was the air curtain mounted over the front door that threatened to blow away all napkins on the table with a cool gust of wind every time the door opened even though we were seated halfway to the counter. It then stays on for several seconds after the door closes and given the relatively small seating area and high traffic at dinner time this was several times a minute. Between the noise and the breeze it really ruined the experience.

Sticky's Finger Joint, advertised as "The best damn chicken finger you have ever tasted!" but not quite so, a mutual consensus among my friends.  Inside the joint, the atmosphere is noisy with loud music and groups of young people chilling. We ordered 3 medium baskets of chicken poppers, chicken fingers, and cajun fries. For sauces, we chose Chipotle aioli (advertised as spicy, but not the least bit of spicy), buttermilk baby ranch, and Sticky's sauce (creamy white BBQ sauce). While the cajun fries were standard and on par with what we expected, chicken from other chicken places are much much better. The chicken was semi-crunchy on the outside and flavorless on the inside. Some seasoning would be nice. All of the sauces were lacking in flavor as well, so stock up on ketchup! At least the chicken wasn't dry. We vouch for Popeyes for having better chicken!

One of my favorite foods, if not my favorite, is fried chicken. I'm always craving it, so I came over to Sticky's on my lunch break to meet up with a friend and get my fried chicken fix.  The idea behind Sticky's is simple - choose your size, choose the type of chicken you want, and choose a sauce. They have tons of sauces - everything from a safe standby BBQ sauce to Buffalo Balsamic Maple (homemade buffalo with balsamic and maple syrup) and Vindaloo BBQ (vinegar bbq with spicy indian curry).  The chicken comes out absolutely piping hot and crispy, just the way I like it. The line for this place during lunches can get long, but it moves fast. Keep in mind there's very limited seating inside, so you may have to take your food on the run if all the seats are taken.  Bottom line: the price is right and the chicken is crispy. I'll be back.
